---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageHeader from "../components/PageHeader.astro";
import CertificationsStrip from "../components/CertificationsStrip.astro";
import CTABand from "../components/CTABand.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Peregrine Systems"
  description="Peregrine Systems is a senior-led Salesforce practice for teams from small to enterprise. Built around two pillars: True Consulting and System Clarity."
>
  <PageHeader
    eyebrow="About"
    title="A senior-led Salesforce practice."
    lede="We help growing and enterprise teams get more out of Salesforce through consulting that challenges assumptions, systems built for real operations, and documentation that makes the org understandable to everyone who depends on it."
  />

  {/* What we do — the two named pillars carry this section. */}
  <section class="section">
    <div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-6xl px-5 sm:px-8">
      <div class="grid gap-10 md:grid-cols-[minmax(0,0.9fr)_minmax(0,1.1fr)] md:items-end">
        <div>
          <span class="eyebrow">What we do</span>
          <h2 class="mt-4 text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl">Two pillars.</h2>
          <span class="rule-divider mt-6"></span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-ink-muted)] md:max-w-prose">
          Most of what makes our approach different comes down to two ideas. 
          First: the conversation that should happen before anything gets built. 
          Second: making the system understandable after it’s live.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 grid gap-px overflow-hidden rounded border border-[color:var(--color-rule)] bg-[color:var(--color-rule)] sm:grid-cols-2">
        <article class="bg-[color:var(--color-cream)] p-8">
          <span class="font-[Michroma,sans-serif] text-xs tracking-[0.3em] text-[color:var(--color-gold)]">01</span>
          <h3 class="mt-3 text-2xl">True Consulting</h3>
          <div class="mt-4 space-y-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-ink-2)]">
            <p>
              We push back before we build. The wrong request, executed cleanly, is still the wrong outcome. 
              We challenge assumptions early and design solutions that scale operationally, not just technically.
            </p>
            <p>
              The result is less rework, fewer reversals, and systems that continue to hold up as the business grows.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="bg-[color:var(--color-cream)] p-8">
          <span class="font-[Michroma,sans-serif] text-xs tracking-[0.3em] text-[color:var(--color-gold)]">02</span>
          <h3 class="mt-3 text-2xl">System Clarity</h3>
          <div class="mt-4 space-y-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-ink-2)]">
            <p>
              Most Salesforce documentation lives in silos — process in one place, automation in another. 
              We deliver a single visual system map that connects the business process to the underlying automation.
            </p>
            <p>
              Leadership sees how the system actually operates. Developers understand where new functionality 
              intersects with existing workflows. Teams make decisions with a shared understanding of the org instead of tribal knowledge.
            </p>
          </div>
          <a
            href="/system-mapping"
            class="mt-6 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-[color:var(--color-gold)] link-underline"
          >
            See System Mapping <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
          </a>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* How we do it — operating posture. */}
  <section class="section bg-[color:var(--color-cream-2)]">
    <div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-6xl px-5 sm:px-8">
      <div class="text-center">
        <span class="eyebrow">How we do it</span>
        <h2 class="mt-4 text-3xl sm:text-4xl">How the work actually runs.</h2>
        <span class="rule-divider rule-divider-center mt-6"></span>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-14 grid gap-10 md:grid-cols-3">
        <article class="relative pl-6 border-l border-[color:var(--color-gold)]/60">
          <div class="font-[Michroma,sans-serif] text-xs tracking-[0.3em] text-[color:var(--color-gold)]">01</div>
          <h3 class="mt-3 text-xl leading-snug">Senior consultants. With your users.</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-ink-muted)]">
            You work directly with the senior consultant — and they work directly with your users.
            No layered staffing, no junior account team between us and the people using the system.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="relative pl-6 border-l border-[color:var(--color-gold)]/60">
          <div class="font-[Michroma,sans-serif] text-xs tracking-[0.3em] text-[color:var(--color-gold)]">02</div>
          <h3 class="mt-3 text-xl leading-snug">Configure before you code.</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-ink-muted)]">
            We exhaust declarative tools before reaching for Apex. Cleaner systems, lower maintenance overhead, 
            and an org your future admin can actually manage.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="relative pl-6 border-l border-[color:var(--color-gold)]/60">
          <div class="font-[Michroma,sans-serif] text-xs tracking-[0.3em] text-[color:var(--color-gold)]">03</div>
          <h3 class="mt-3 text-xl leading-snug">Outcomes over hours.</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-ink-muted)]">
            We scope toward the operational result, not open-ended time. 
            You know what’s being delivered, why it matters, and what it costs before work begins.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* Why we do it — mission, then wedge. */}
  <section class="section">
    <div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-5xl px-5 sm:px-8">
      <div class="text-center">
        <span class="eyebrow">Why we do it</span>
        <h2 class="mt-4 text-3xl sm:text-4xl">Why Peregrine Systems.</h2>
        <span class="rule-divider rule-divider-center mt-6"></span>
      </div>

      <div class="mx-auto mt-10 max-w-2xl space-y-5 text-base leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-ink-2)]">
        {/* TODO: Replace mission paragraph with client-approved wording (open input #2). */}
        <p>
          We started Peregrine Systems to run Salesforce engagements the way we believe they should be run: 
          senior operators owning the work end-to-end, honest conversations about what actually needs to be built, 
          and systems designed to remain understandable as the business evolves.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our background is in building and operating systems, not just configuring software. 
          We approach Salesforce as operational infrastructure — something teams rely on every day to make decisions, 
          coordinate work, and keep the business moving.
        </p>
        <p>
          Much of the industry optimizes for scale on the consulting side instead of clarity on the client side. 
          Calls go unanswered. Work gets handed downward. The senior expert from the pitch disappears once the contract is signed.
        </p>
        <p>
          We built Peregrine Systems for organizations that want direct access to experienced builders — consultants who understand operations, 
          think critically before implementation, and stay accountable for the outcome.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CertificationsStrip />
  <CTABand />
</BaseLayout>
